Descriptor.0: ECT-HOPE-Sci-L2>ECT Helium Oxygen Proton Electron Plasma Analyszer Level 2

Logical_source_description.0: Spin resolved ECT-HOPE science data. Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV, ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.

Acknowledgement.0: Herb Funsten, Ruth Skoug, Reiner Friedel

LINK_TITLE.2: Science Gateway (including Mission Rules of the Road for Data Usage)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Detector_LABL
Sector_LABL
Energy_LABL
Detector No.
Sector No.
Collapse method used for a given pixel.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: For a given pixel, the number of spin angle sectors which are collapsed on board to fit the telemetry allocation. The collapse method sums all values together, then compresses according to the following algorithm: if (sum < 16384) {return sum} else {return ((sum-16384)/64) + 16384}

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ESA_Volt_LABL_1
Acquisition_Period

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The length of a single ESA step acquisition

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Science data acquisition Plan

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Which science plan was used for the acquisition.  The seclected science plan determines the ESA Sweep, TOF DAC, data product selection, and data collapse method used for an acquisition.  As a general rule, plans 0-7 & 15 are reserved for HOPE nominal operations, and 8-14 are reserved for burst support operations.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Plan_Step

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Which step within a science plan was used.  Each science plan consists of up to 16 steps, each of which can specify different HVPS and telemetry configuration settings.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ESA_Volt

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Absolute values of the ESA voltage that was used for each energy step.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: [CreateCDF ONLY] FPDU: Differential directional proton flux ~15-50,000 eV (5 Detectors, 16 Sectors, 72 Energies)

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Proton flux as a function of detector pixel (5), spin angle sector (16), and energy (72).  Note that data have been expanded to the highest possible resolution (16 spin angles, 72 energies), even though in most cases the transmitted data are collapsed (36 energies, 4-8-16-8-4 spin angles) to fit the telemetry allocation.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flags to indicate potential issues with the ion data. Each element of this array contains the flag status for a particular concern.
